  "note": "Phase 6 Task 7. Single case constructs an AlternativeComparisonReportResults directly via the internal (withProjectAlternativeResults, withoutProjectAlternativeResults, eqadResults, baseYearEADResults, futureYearEADResults) ctor. `with_project` is a list of two AlternativeResults entries (alternative_id 1 and 2), each built the same way alternative_results.json's cases are: the (StudyAreaConsequencesByQuantile, id, analysisYears, periodOfAnalysis, isNull) 'public for testing' ctor for the AlternativeResults-level `eqad_results` field, then BaseYearScenarioResults/FutureYearScenarioResults assigned from `base_year_impact_areas`/`future_year_impact_areas` (each in the exact impact_area_scenario_results.json construct/consequence_realizations/aep_observations/stage_observations shape, one ImpactAreaScenarioResults per entry, AddResults'd into a fresh ScenarioResults in order -- identical helper reuse to alternative_results.json), and ScenariosAreIdentical=false. `without_project` is one more AlternativeResults built the same way (its own alternative_id is irrelevant -- never read by any delegator under test). `eqad_reduced_results_list`/`base_year_ead_reduced_results_list`/`future_year_ead_reduced_results_list` are each a list of {alternative_id, consequence_results} objects: for each, a StudyAreaConsequencesByQuantile is built via the (int alternativeID) ctor (the ONLY ctor that sets a real, non-zero AlternativeID) then AddExistingConsequenceResultObject-ed with the per-entry AggregatedConsequencesByQuantile results (study_area_consequences_by_quantile.json-shaped, Empirical.SampleMean force-set to each entry's own `sample_mean` field, same convention as alternative_results.json/study_area_consequences_by_quantile.json) -- this is the ONLY construction path in the real C# that produces a StudyAreaConsequencesByQuantile with both a populated ConsequenceResultList AND a meaningful AlternativeID, matching how AlternativeComparisonReport (Task 10, not yet ported) is expected to build these lists incrementally. `method` dispatches (args documented per-assertion below; ConsequenceType.Damage/RiskType.Total implicit at every level, matching how every ScenarioResults realization and reduced-results entry was built): alternative_id-taking methods (`sample_mean_eqad_reduced`/`sample_mean_base_year_ead_reduced`/`sample_mean_future_year_ead_reduced`/`sample_mean_with_project_base_year_ead`/`sample_mean_with_project_future_year_ead`/histogram-sample-mean siblings) take args=[alternative_id, damage_category_or_null, asset_category_or_null, impact_area_id]; the without-project delegators (`sample_mean_without_project_base_year_ead`/`sample_mean_without_project_future_year_ead`) take args=[damage_category_or_null, asset_category_or_null, impact_area_id] (no alternative_id -- they read `_WithoutProjectAlternativeResults` directly, proving the with/without delegation split independent of `get_consequences_reduced_results_for_given_alternative`'s list-selection logic). Exercises both with-project alternatives (1 and 2) against all three reduced-results lists, proving `get_consequences_reduced_results_for_given_alternative`'s per-alternative linear search across each of the three independently-populated lists. All values PIN, gate-captured, never hand-derived (every assertion routes through real ScenarioResults consequence-histogram binning or Empirical stacking, not a simple average of raw inputs).",
